==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Britishism
<hw>Britishism</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>an expression that is
limited to English as spoken by Englishmen (especially as contrasted
with American English).</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Anglicism, Briticism.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a custom that is peculiar to England or its
citizens.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Anglicism.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Briton</ent>⟦br⟧
